                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 839.00/1018.</note>
                <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Santo Domingo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1913-12-19">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 19, 1913</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The three delegates of the Department ask me to report that they have completed
                    their labors and will sail today: Stabler for Port au Prince, Gibson and
                    Sterling via Cuba for Washington.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Sullivan</hi>.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
